data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value:
If the maximum penalty for 1000 words is set to 10 and the total number of words in a document is equal to 1200, then the following calculation applies:
1. Get the minimum allowable penalty for a single word 0.01 = 10 / 1000
2. Get the minimum allowable penalty for the document (considering the total number of words) 12 = 0.01 X 1200
3. If the sum of the Quality Metric penalties are greater than 12, then the quality assessment fails!
